     <div type="dedication">
   <pb n="93" facs="52"/>
   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <p>To controll those false copyes of this ser<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>mon,
which were printed without my
knowledge, (patched) as it seemeth out of
some borrowed notes,<note place="margin">Gen. 43. 11.</note> and to stop the prin<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ting
of it again without my corrections, as
it was intēded, because they had got it licē<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ced
before, although vt <gap reason="illegible" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>erly vnwilling for
some respectes to haue it published, whiche
made me withstand their importunitie so
long, yet seeing more inconuenience then I
thought of, I suffered that which I could
not hinder. And nowe hoping that it is
Gods will to profite some by it, as <hi>Iacob</hi>
parted from <hi>Beniamin,</hi> so that which
must be, let be, and the Lord giue thee a
blessing with it.</p>
</div>
